                <note rend="inline" type="source">825.001 Montero, Juan/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Chile</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Culbertson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-08-18T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >August 18, 1931—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>95. Montero accepted yesterday the presidential nomination made by all political
                    parties except those of the extreme Left. In order not to establish the
                    precedent of chief executive being a candidate for the presidency he indicated
                    immediately his intention to tender his resignation as Vice President but has
                    deferred action and at present it seems that there will be some delay in
                    determining who will succeed him as Vice President. In the meantime Montero will
                    hold over.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Culbertson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
